    • Constructor Detail

      • YRCCalendarInputObj

        public YRCCalendarInputObj(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Control control,
                           java.util.Date disableBeforeDate,
                           java.util.Date disableAfterDate,
                           java.lang.String dateFormatter,
                           java.util.Date dateSelected)
        Constructor of the Input Object used to display Calendar in the screen.
        Parameters:
        control - can be either a label or Text or null. if null, the date selected will be returned and not set on any control. The Calendar pop up will appear at the center of the screen area. If any particular location is desired the x-coordinate and y-coordinate should set using using the setters exposed in this object.
        disableBeforeDate - is date before which date's will be disabled.
        disableAfterDate - is date after which date's will be disabled.
        dateFormatter - is custom date formatter which Calendar will make use of to display the date.
        dateSelected - is the date which will be selected in the calendar by default in the absence of a control or when there is no date set to the control. For a date to get selected it should be within the range, if it is specified. Current Date gets selected when there is no date set to the control and when no default date is specified as argument in the constructor.

      • YRCCalendarInputObj

        public YRCCalendarInputObj(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Control control,
                           IYRCCalendarDateValidator dateValidator,
                           java.lang.String dateFormatter,
                           java.util.Date dateSelected)
        Parameters:
        control - can be either a label or Text or null. if null, the date selected will be returned and not set on any control. The Calendar pop up will appear at the center of the screen area. If any particular location is desired the x-coordinate and y-coordinate should set using using the setters exposed in this object.
        dateValidator - custom date validator which can be implemented to enable/disable date's IYRCCalendarDateValidator
        dateFormatter - is custom date formatter which Calendar will make use of to display the date.
        dateSelected - is the date which will be selected in the calendar by default in the absence of a control or when there is no date set to the control. For a date to get selected it should be within the range, if it is specified. Current Date gets selected when there is no date set to the control and when no default date is specified as argument in the constructor.
